Note:
==============================================================================
FALCON-LDL : LDL decomposition tree for the Falcon trapdoor sampler
==============================================================================

Per Falcon spec section 3.8.3 ("ffLDL Tree"), the secret-key trapdoor
basis B = [[g, -f], [G, -F]] generates a Gram matrix

    Gtilde = B * B^H = [[ |g|^2 + |G|^2 ,  -(g*f_bar + G*F_bar) ],
                       [ -(g_bar*f + G_bar*F), |f|^2 + |F|^2 ]]

in the cyclotomic FFT domain.  Its LDL decomposition Gtilde = L * D * L^H
with L unit-lower-triangular and D diagonal is unique and is the entry
point for the Fast Fourier Sampler:

  L = [[1,    0],
       [L10,  1]]

  D = diag(D0, D1)

where
  D0   = Gtilde[0,0]
  L10  = Gtilde[1,0] / D0
  D1   = Gtilde[1,1] - L10 * conj(L10) * D0

The Falcon FFS recurses on the diagonal entries D0 and D1: each is split
into half-size cyclotomic representations and the LDL decomposition is
applied again at the smaller ring.  At the leaves (n = 1) the tree stores
the standard deviation sigma = sqrt(D_leaf) which the integer Gaussian
sampler uses directly.

Tree node layout in memory (allocated per-node from the arena):
  Offset  0:   pointer to L10 FFT buffer (16*n bytes of complex Float64)
               -- only present for internal nodes (n >= 2)
  Offset  8:   pointer to D0 FFT buffer (16*n_half bytes), real coefficients
               -- pre-split into the half-size domain
  Offset 16:   pointer to D1 FFT buffer (16*n_half bytes), real coefficients
  Offset 24:   pointer to left subtree (LDL tree on D0 at size n_half)
  Offset 32:   pointer to right subtree (LDL tree on D1 at size n_half)
  Offset 40:   the n associated with this node, stored as Integer (8 bytes)
  Offset 48:   leaf-flag (1 if this is the n=1 leaf, else 0)
  Offset 56:   leaf-only: sigma value (Float64) for the integer sampler

Total node header size: 64 bytes plus the variable-length FFT buffers.

This module depends on falcon_fft.runa (forward/inverse FFT, pointwise
ops), falcon_fp.runa (Float64 arithmetic), and the standard memory/arena
primitives.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/pq/falcon_fp.runa" as FP
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/pq/falcon_fft.runa" as FFT

Note:
==============================================================================
Constants for the Falcon-spec sigma parameters used at leaves
==============================================================================
sigma_min is encoded here as a Float64 derived from Falcon's published
constants.  Falcon-512 uses sigma_min = 1.2778, Falcon-1024 uses
sigma_min = 1.298.  We expose level-dispatched accessors.
:End Note

Process called "ldl_sigma_min_512" returns Float:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the Falcon-512 sigma_min as IEEE 754 binary64 (Pornin
    reference fpr_sigma_min[9]).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bit pattern 4608433670533905013 = 0x3FF47201BF1F7A75 decodes to
    1.2778336969128337 (decimal) -- the per-logn smoothing-parameter
    based sigma_min from the Falcon round-3 specification at logn=9.
    This is the exact constant from Pornin's reference fpr.h::fpr_sigma_min[9].
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public constant.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return 4608433670533905013
End Process

Process called "ldl_sigma_min_1024" returns Float:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the Falcon-1024 sigma_min as IEEE 754 binary64 (Pornin
    reference fpr_sigma_min[10]).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bit pattern 4608525754002622308 = 0x3FF4C5C19990C764 decodes to
    1.298280334344292 (decimal) -- the per-logn sigma_min from the
    Falcon round-3 specification at logn=10.  This is the exact constant
    from Pornin's reference fpr.h::fpr_sigma_min[10].
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public constant.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return 4608525754002622308
End Process

Process called "ldl_sigma_min_for_n" takes n as Integer returns Float:
    @Reasoning
    Dispatches between Falcon-512 and Falcon-1024 sigma_min.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    n=512 -> Falcon-512 constant, n=1024 -> Falcon-1024 constant.
    For intermediate tree levels (n < 512) the Falcon spec uses the
    same sigma_min as the top level since the recursion preserves
    the smoothing parameter bound.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public.
    @End Security_Scope
    If n is greater than or equal to 1024:
        Return proc ldl_sigma_min_1024
    End If
    Return proc ldl_sigma_min_512
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
GLOBAL TRAPDOOR SIGMA (fpr_inv_sigma[logn] in Pornin reference)
==============================================================================
The Falcon spec uses a global trapdoor sigma (sigma_global) that drives
the per-leaf normalization.  Each leaf stores the isigma value
   isigma_leaf = sqrt(D_leaf[0]) / sigma_global
which the integer sampler consumes directly as 1/sigma_effective.  The
sigma_global value for Falcon-N is the same one used in the reference
constant table fpr_inv_sigma[logn], decoded from the published bit
patterns:
   logn=9 (n=512)  : bit pattern 4573606369665796042, value ~0.006033669668
                     (1/sigma_global ~ 165.7366)
   logn=10 (n=1024): bit pattern 4573496814039276259, value ~0.005938645310
                     (1/sigma_global ~ 168.3886)
We expose the value of 1/sigma_global as a Float since that is the form
required by the leaf normalization (sigma_leaf_stored = sqrt(D) * inv_sigma_global).
:End Note

Process called "ldl_inv_sigma_global_512" returns Float:
    @Reasoning
    Returns 1/sigma_global for Falcon-512 as IEEE 754 binary64.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bit pattern 4573606369665796042 from Pornin reference fpr_inv_sigma[9].
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public constant.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return 4573606369665796042
End Process

Process called "ldl_inv_sigma_global_1024" returns Float:
    @Reasoning
    Returns 1/sigma_global for Falcon-1024 as IEEE 754 binary64.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bit pattern 4573496814039276259 from Pornin reference fpr_inv_sigma[10].
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public constant.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return 4573496814039276259
End Process

Process called "ldl_inv_sigma_global_for_n" takes n as Integer returns Float:
    @Reasoning
    Dispatches 1/sigma_global between Falcon-512 and Falcon-1024.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    n >= 1024 -> Falcon-1024 constant, otherwise Falcon-512 constant.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public.
    @End Security_Scope
    If n is greater than or equal to 1024:
        Return proc ldl_inv_sigma_global_1024
    End If
    Return proc ldl_inv_sigma_global_512
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
TREE NODE FIELD ACCESSORS
==============================================================================
:End Note

Process called "ldl_tree_L01" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Pointer to the L10 FFT buffer (offset 0).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single qword load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Internal.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return Memory.memory_get_pointer(tree, 0)
End Process

Process called "ldl_tree_D0" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Pointer to the D0 FFT buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Qword load at offset 8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Internal.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return Memory.memory_get_pointer(tree, 8)
End Process

Process called "ldl_tree_D1" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Pointer to the D1 FFT buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
