Note:
==============================================================================
RECURSIVE LDL OF A SINGLE-DIMENSIONAL POSITIVE-REAL POLYNOMIAL
==============================================================================
This is the "ffLDL_internal" routine of the Falcon reference.  It takes a
length-n FFT-domain polynomial G (which must be a positive-real diagonal
entry derived from the Gram matrix in the parent step) and:

  1. Splits G into two half-size representations G_e and G_o via the
     Falcon "fft split" formula (see Falcon spec sec 2.3 splitfft / mergefft).
  2. Sets L10 = G_o * G_e^{-1}  (a complex-valued half-size FFT polynomial).
  3. Sets D0 = G_e, D1 = G_o - L10 * conj(L10) * G_e.
  4. Recurses on D0, D1 at size n/2.
  5. At n = 1, stores sigma = sqrt(D) and marks the node as a leaf.
:End Note

Note:
==============================================================================
FFT SPLIT / MERGE (Falcon spec section 2.3)
==============================================================================
For an FFT-domain polynomial f over K_n = Q[X]/(X^n+1), the splitfft
operator produces two half-size FFT-domain polynomials f_e, f_o over
K_{n/2} = Q[Y]/(Y^(n/2)+1) such that f(X) = f_e(X^2) + X * f_o(X^2)
in coefficient form.

In FFT representation the formula is:

  f_e[k] = (f[k] + f[k + n/2]) / 2
  f_o[k] = ((f[k] - f[k + n/2]) / 2) * conj(zeta_k)

where zeta_k = exp(i * (2k+1) * pi / n) is the k-th primitive 2n-th
root of unity at the odd position (the same indexing used by
fft_forward above).
:End Note

Process called "ldl_fft_split" takes arena as Integer, src as Integer, n as Integer, fe as Integer, fo as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    FFT split into K_{n/2} pair. Our forward FFT outputs slots in
    bit-reversed order (slot k holds f(zeta_{rev(k)})). For the
    K_n -> K_{n/2} decomposition along z² substitution, the paired
    eval points zeta_a and zeta_{a+hn} live at INTERLEAVED slot
    indices (2u, 2u+1), not at distant indices (k, k+hn). The split
    therefore pairs consecutive even/odd slots and uses a twiddle
    indexed by the bit-reversal of u.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Per Falcon spec sec 2.3 splitfft formula (Pornin reference
    poly_split_fft, fft.c).  For u in [0, n/2):
      a_complex = src[2u]
      b_complex = src[2u+1]
      fe[u]     = (a + b) / 2
      twiddle   = conj(zeta_{rev_logn(2u)}) where rev_logn is
                  bit-reversal over logn bits. Note rev_logn(2u) =
                  rev_{logn-1}(u) since the low bit of 2u is 0.
      fo[u]     = ((a - b) / 2) * twiddle
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(n) with n/2 cos/sin evaluations on the twiddle path.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Operands SECRET; deterministic in n.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let half_n be n shifted right by 1
    Let two_v be FP.fp_from_int(2)
    Let n_f be FP.fp_from_int(n)
    Let pi_v be FP.fp_pi()
    Note: logn_minus_1 = log2(n) - 1
    Let logn_minus_1 be 0
    Let tmp_n be half_n
    While tmp_n is greater than 1:
        Set logn_minus_1 to logn_minus_1 plus 1
        Set tmp_n to tmp_n shifted right by 1
    End While
    Let u be 0
    While u is less than half_n:
        Let slot_a be u multiplied by 2
        Let slot_b be slot_a plus 1
        Let ar be FFT.fft_get_real(src, slot_a)
        Let ai be FFT.fft_get_imag(src, slot_a)
        Let br be FFT.fft_get_real(src, slot_b)
        Let bi be FFT.fft_get_imag(src, slot_b)

        Let sr be FP.fp_add(ar, br)
        Let si be FP.fp_add(ai, bi)
        Let dr be FP.fp_sub(ar, br)
        Let di be FP.fp_sub(ai, bi)
        Let fe_r be FP.fp_div(sr, two_v)
        Let fe_i be FP.fp_div(si, two_v)
        Let dr_half be FP.fp_div(dr, two_v)
        Let di_half be FP.fp_div(di, two_v)

        Note: twiddle conj(zeta_a) = cos(theta) - i*sin(theta) with
        Note: theta = (2*a + 1) * pi / n where a = rev_{logn-1}(u).
        Let a_idx be proc FFT.fft_bit_reverse with u, logn_minus_1
        Let two_a_plus_1 be 2 multiplied by a_idx plus 1
        Let ta_f be FP.fp_from_int(two_a_plus_1)
        Let prod1 be FP.fp_mul(ta_f, pi_v)
        Let theta be FP.fp_div(prod1, n_f)
        Let cr be FP.fp_cos(theta)
        Let ci_neg be FP.fp_sin(theta)
        Let ci be FP.fp_neg(ci_neg)

        Note: fo = (dr_half + di_half*i) * (cr + ci*i)
        Note:    = (dr_half*cr - di_half*ci) + (dr_half*ci + di_half*cr) i
        Let m1 be FP.fp_mul(dr_half, cr)
        Let m2 be FP.fp_mul(di_half, ci)
        Let fo_r be FP.fp_sub(m1, m2)
        Let m3 be FP.fp_mul(dr_half, ci)
        Let m4 be FP.fp_mul(di_half, cr)
        Let fo_i be FP.fp_add(m3, m4)

        FFT.fft_set_real(fe, u, fe_r)
        FFT.fft_set_imag(fe, u, fe_i)
        FFT.fft_set_real(fo, u, fo_r)
        FFT.fft_set_imag(fo, u, fo_i)

        Set u to u plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
GRAM MATRIX COMPUTATION
==============================================================================
Build the 2x2 Hermitian Gram matrix in the FFT domain over K_n.
ldl_gram_diag computes |a|^2 + |b|^2 (a real-positive diagonal entry).
ldl_gram_off_diag computes a*conj(b) + c*conj(d) (a complex off-diagonal).
The caller chooses which polynomials map to which slot per the Falcon
ROW convention (see ldl_build_tree).
:End Note

Process called "ldl_gram_diag" takes arena as Integer, a_fft as Integer, b_fft as Integer, n as Integer, out as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compute |a|^2 + |b|^2 in the FFT domain into the real-valued out buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    For each k: out[k] = a_r^2 + a_i^2 + b_r^2 + b_i^2 (real), zero imag.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(n).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let k be 0
    While k is less than n:
        Let ar be FFT.fft_get_real(a_fft, k)
        Let ai be FFT.fft_get_imag(a_fft, k)
        Let br be FFT.fft_get_real(b_fft, k)
        Let bi be FFT.fft_get_imag(b_fft, k)
        Let ar2 be FP.fp_mul(ar, ar)
        Let ai2 be FP.fp_mul(ai, ai)
        Let br2 be FP.fp_mul(br, br)
        Let bi2 be FP.fp_mul(bi, bi)
        Let s1 be FP.fp_add(ar2, ai2)
        Let s2 be FP.fp_add(br2, bi2)
        Let total be FP.fp_add(s1, s2)
        FFT.fft_set_real(out, k, total)
        Let zv be FP.fp_zero()
        FFT.fft_set_imag(out, k, zv)
        Set k to k plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "ldl_gram_off_diag" takes arena as Integer, a_fft as Integer, b_fft as Integer, c_fft as Integer, d_fft as Integer, n as Integer, out as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compute  a * conj(b) + c * conj(d)  in the FFT domain.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    For each k:
      (a + ai)(br - bi*i) = (a_r*br + a_i*bi) + (a_i*br - a_r*bi)i
      Similarly for c*conj(d).  Sum into out.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(n) with 8 mulsd + several adds per coefficient.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let k be 0
    While k is less than n:
        Let ar be FFT.fft_get_real(a_fft, k)
        Let ai be FFT.fft_get_imag(a_fft, k)
        Let br be FFT.fft_get_real(b_fft, k)
        Let bi be FFT.fft_get_imag(b_fft, k)
        Let cr be FFT.fft_get_real(c_fft, k)
        Let ci be FFT.fft_get_imag(c_fft, k)
        Let dr be FFT.fft_get_real(d_fft, k)
        Let di be FFT.fft_get_imag(d_fft, k)
        Let ab_r1 be FP.fp_mul(ar, br)
        Let ab_r2 be FP.fp_mul(ai, bi)
        Let ab_r be FP.fp_add(ab_r1, ab_r2)
        Let ab_i1 be FP.fp_mul(ai, br)
        Let ab_i2 be FP.fp_mul(ar, bi)
        Let ab_i be FP.fp_sub(ab_i1, ab_i2)
        Let cd_r1 be FP.fp_mul(cr, dr)
        Let cd_r2 be FP.fp_mul(ci, di)
        Let cd_r be FP.fp_add(cd_r1, cd_r2)
        Let cd_i1 be FP.fp_mul(ci, dr)
        Let cd_i2 be FP.fp_mul(cr, di)
        Let cd_i be FP.fp_sub(cd_i1, cd_i2)
        Let total_r be FP.fp_add(ab_r, cd_r)
        Let total_i be FP.fp_add(ab_i, cd_i)
        FFT.fft_set_real(out, k, total_r)
        FFT.fft_set_imag(out, k, total_i)
        Set k to k plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
INTERNAL FFLDL RECURSION (Pornin two-polynomial form)
==============================================================================
ldl_internal(g0, g1, n): given an FFT-domain pair (g0, g1) over K_n,
build a Falcon LDL tree node whose at-this-node L10 lives in K_n and
whose children recurse over the split halves of d00 and d11.

This is the EXPLICIT two-polynomial recursion of Pornin's reference
ffLDL_fft_inner (sign.c).  At each call the input (g0, g1) represents
the off-diagonal pair of an implied 2x2 Hermitian Gram
    [[ g0, g1 ],
     [ conj(g1), g0 ]]
(i.e. g11 = g0 = d00 carried down from the parent's split).  The LDL
decomposition of this Gram is

    L10 = g1 / g0                (complex polynomial in K_n)
    d11 = g0 - |g1|^2 / g0        (real polynomial in K_n)

The node stores L10 at FULL size n (Pornin convention: l10 has the same
dimension as the polynomial-pair at the node).  Children are built by
splitting d00=g0 and d11 into K_{n/2} pairs and recursing with each pair.
:End Note

Process called "ldl_internal" takes arena as Integer, g0_fft as Integer, g1_fft as Integer, n as Integer, orig_n as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Pornin reference ffLDL_fft_inner (sign.c).  Builds the LDL subtree
    rooted at the polynomial pair (g0, g1) over K_n.  The implied 2x2
    Gram is [[g0, g1], [conj(g1), g0]] with d00 = g11 = g0.  orig_n is
    the top-level dimension used for leaf normalization.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Leaf case (n == 1):
      - Store isigma = sqrt(g0[0]) * (1/sigma_global(orig_n))  matching
        Pornin's ffLDL_binary_normalize.  g1 is unused at the leaf since
        the leaf's stored value is purely the d00 entry; g1 contributes
        to its sibling subtree via the splitting at the parent level.
        Negative values from float noise are clamped to zero before the
        square root.

    Internal case (n >= 2):
      - Compute the in-place LDL of the implied [[g0, g1], [conj(g1), g0]]
        Hermitian Gram:
          L10[k] = g1[k] / g0[k]                       (complex K_n)
          d11[k] = g0[k] - |g1[k]|^2 / g0[k]           (real K_n)
        L10 lives in K_n (size n) and is stored at this node.
      - Allocate the two split halves of d00 = g0 (size n/2 each) and
        of d11 (size n/2 each) into fresh arena buffers.
      - Recurse left  with (split-low(d00), split-high(d00), n/2)
      - Recurse right with (split-low(d11), split-high(d11), n/2)
      Pornin's "left" subtree corresponds to the d00 split (the
      polynomial that feeds the t0 sampler), "right" to the d11 split
      (which feeds the t1 sampler).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(n) LDL work at this node plus the split costs; recursion makes
    the total O(n log n) across the whole tree.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    All inputs SECRET; the only branching is on n which is public.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let node be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 64)
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ldl_tree_set_L01 with node, 0
    proc ldl_tree_set_D0 with node, 0
    proc ldl_tree_set_D1 with node, 0
    proc ldl_tree_set_left with node, 0
    proc ldl_tree_set_right with node, 0
    proc ldl_tree_set_n with node, n
    proc ldl_tree_set_is_leaf with node, 0

    If n is equal to 1:
        Let leaf_v be FFT.fft_get_real(g0_fft, 0)
        Note: Clamp negative values to zero (numerical noise can produce
        Note: tiny negative reals in well-conditioned inputs).
        Let zero_v be FP.fp_zero()
        Let neg_v be FP.fp_lt(leaf_v, zero_v)
        If neg_v is equal to 1:
            Set leaf_v to zero_v
        End If
        Note: Store isigma_leaf = sqrt(d00[0]) * (1/sigma_global).  Matches
        Note: Pornin's ffLDL_binary_normalize (sign.c).  g1[0] is not stored
        Note: at this leaf -- it contributes to the SIBLING subtree via the
        Note: parent's split routing.
        Let sqrt_v be FP.fp_sqrt(leaf_v)
        Let inv_sigma_g be proc ldl_inv_sigma_global_for_n with orig_n
        Let isigma_leaf be FP.fp_mul(sqrt_v, inv_sigma_g)
        proc ldl_tree_set_sigma with node, isigma_leaf
        proc ldl_tree_set_is_leaf with node, 1
        Return node
    End If

    Let half_n be n shifted right by 1
    Let full_bytes be n multiplied by 16
    Let half_bytes be half_n multiplied by 16

    Note: Step 1: LDL of the quasicyclic Hermitian 2x2 [[g0, g1], [conj(g1), g0]]
    Note: in K_n.  Per Pornin reference (poly_LDLmv_fft, fft.c):
    Note:   mu     = g01 / g00 = g1 / g0    (full complex divide)
    Note:   d11    = g11 - mu * conj(g01) = g0 - mu * conj(g1)   (complex)
    Note:   l10    = conj(mu)
    Note: g0 is auto-adjoint at the n=initial level (real-valued in our
    Note: layout); after the FFT split into K_{n/2}, the resulting pair
    Note: is GENERALLY COMPLEX at each slot (the auto-adjoint property
    Note: is preserved as a structural property of the pair, not as a
    Note: "real-valued slot" property).  The LDL therefore MUST use full
    Note: complex arithmetic at every internal recursion level; reading
    Note: only g0_re and treating g0_im = 0 produces wrong l10 and d11
    Note: at sub-K_n recursion depths and breaks the sampler for Falcon
    Note: parameters that recurse more than a few levels deep.
    Let L10 be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, full_bytes)
    Let d11 be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, full_bytes)
    If d11 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be 0
    While k is less than n:
        Let g0r be FFT.fft_get_real(g0_fft, k)
        Let g0i be FFT.fft_get_imag(g0_fft, k)
        Let g1r be FFT.fft_get_real(g1_fft, k)
        Let g1i be FFT.fft_get_imag(g1_fft, k)
        Let zero_v be FP.fp_zero()

        Note: |g0|^2 = g0r^2 + g0i^2.
        Let g0_sqr_re be FP.fp_mul(g0r, g0r)
        Let g0_sqr_im be FP.fp_mul(g0i, g0i)
        Let g0_norm2 be FP.fp_add(g0_sqr_re, g0_sqr_im)
        Let g0_is_zero be FP.fp_eq(g0_norm2, zero_v)

        Let mu_r be zero_v
        Let mu_i be zero_v
        Let d11r be g0r
        Let d11i be g0i
        If g0_is_zero is equal to 0:
            Note: mu = g1 / g0 = g1 * conj(g0) / |g0|^2 (complex divide).
            Let num_r_a be FP.fp_mul(g1r, g0r)
            Let num_r_b be FP.fp_mul(g1i, g0i)
            Let num_r be FP.fp_add(num_r_a, num_r_b)
            Let num_i_a be FP.fp_mul(g1i, g0r)
            Let num_i_b be FP.fp_mul(g1r, g0i)
            Let num_i be FP.fp_sub(num_i_a, num_i_b)
            Set mu_r to FP.fp_div(num_r, g0_norm2)
            Set mu_i to FP.fp_div(num_i, g0_norm2)

            Note: subterm = mu * conj(g1) = (mu_r + mu_i*i) * (g1r - g1i*i)
            Note:        = (mu_r*g1r + mu_i*g1i) + (mu_i*g1r - mu_r*g1i)*i
            Let sub_r_a be FP.fp_mul(mu_r, g1r)
            Let sub_r_b be FP.fp_mul(mu_i, g1i)
            Let sub_r be FP.fp_add(sub_r_a, sub_r_b)
            Let sub_i_a be FP.fp_mul(mu_i, g1r)
            Let sub_i_b be FP.fp_mul(mu_r, g1i)
            Let sub_i be FP.fp_sub(sub_i_a, sub_i_b)

            Set d11r to FP.fp_sub(g0r, sub_r)
            Set d11i to FP.fp_sub(g0i, sub_i)
        End If
        Note: l10 = conj(mu) = (mu_r, -mu_i).
        Let neg_mu_i be FP.fp_neg(mu_i)
        FFT.fft_set_real(L10, k, mu_r)
        FFT.fft_set_imag(L10, k, neg_mu_i)
        FFT.fft_set_real(d11, k, d11r)
        FFT.fft_set_imag(d11, k, d11i)
        Set k to k plus 1
    End While
    proc ldl_tree_set_L01 with node, L10

    Note: Step 2: split d00 = g0 into two K_{n/2} polynomials (d00_e, d00_o).
    Let d00_e be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, half_bytes)
    Let d00_o be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, half_bytes)
    If d00_o is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ldl_fft_split with arena, g0_fft, n, d00_e, d00_o

    Note: Step 3: split d11 into (d11_e, d11_o) in K_{n/2}.
    Let d11_e be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, half_bytes)
    Let d11_o be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, half_bytes)
    If d11_o is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ldl_fft_split with arena, d11, n, d11_e, d11_o

    Note: Step 4: recurse.  Left subtree carries the d00 split (feeds the
    Note: t0 sampler); right subtree carries the d11 split (feeds t1).
    Let left_child be proc ldl_internal with arena, d00_e, d00_o, half_n, orig_n
    If left_child is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let right_child be proc ldl_internal with arena, d11_e, d11_o, half_n, orig_n
    If right_child is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ldl_tree_set_left with node, left_child
    proc ldl_tree_set_right with node, right_child
    Return node
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
TOP-LEVEL FFLDL CONSTRUCTION
==============================================================================
ldl_build_tree(f, g, F, G, n): Falcon-spec Algorithm 8 (entry).  Computes
the Gram matrix of the basis B = [[g, -f], [G, -F]] in the FFT domain,
performs the 2x2 LDL split, and recurses on D0 and D1.
:End Note

Process called "ldl_build_tree" takes arena as Integer, f_int as Integer, g_int as Integer, F_int as Integer, G_int as Integer, n as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Build the Falcon LDL tree for the trapdoor basis B = [[g, -f], [G, -F]]
    rooted at the basis-level 2x2 Gram and recursing down to leaves via
    Pornin's explicit two-polynomial ffLDL_fft recursion (sign.c).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Algorithm 8 (Falcon spec) / Pornin reference ffLDL_fft (sign.c):

    1. FFT-load f, g, F, G and run the forward FFT to length n.

    2. Compute the 2x2 Hermitian Gram of the row basis B = [[g, -f], [G, -F]]
       in K_n:
         gram_00 = <row0, row0> = |g|^2 + |f|^2       (real)
         gram_11 = <row1, row1> = |G|^2 + |F|^2       (real)
         gram_10 = <row1, row0> = G*conj(g) + F*conj(f)  (complex)

    3. In-place LDL at the top: with g00 = gram_00 (real-positive), g01 =
       gram_10, g11 = gram_11:
         L01_top[k] = g01[k] / g00[k]    (complex K_n divide; g00 real)
         d11[k]     = g11[k] - |g01[k]|^2 / g00[k]    (real K_n)
       L01_top is the at-node l10 of the top node and is stored at full
       size n (matching Pornin's tree[0..n-1]).

    4. Split d00 = gram_00 into K_{n/2} pair (d00_e, d00_o); split d11
       into (d11_e, d11_o).  Recurse:
         left  subtree = ldl_internal(d00_e, d00_o, n/2)
         right subtree = ldl_internal(d11_e, d11_o, n/2)

    This is structurally identical to Pornin's ffLDL_fft (sign.c lines
    ~360-405) up to the FFT layout convention.  All multiplications and
    divides at the top happen in K_n (size n FFT) so the subsequent
    sampler can do its K_n multiplications against L01_top without
    losing the structural equivalence between split(t * l10) and
    split(t) * split(l10) under K_{n/2}-arithmetic.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(n log n) total; O(n) per level for the LDL + splits.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    All inputs SECRET; loop bounds depend on n which is public.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let bytes be n multiplied by 16
    Let half_n be n shifted right by 1
    Let half_bytes be half_n multiplied by 16

    Let f_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bytes)
    Let g_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bytes)
    Let F_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bytes)
    Let G_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bytes)
    If G_fft is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    FFT.fft_load_from_int16_signed(f_int, f_fft, n)
    FFT.fft_load_from_int16_signed(g_int, g_fft, n)
    FFT.fft_load_from_int16_signed(F_int, F_fft, n)
    FFT.fft_load_from_int16_signed(G_int, G_fft, n)
    FFT.fft_forward(arena, f_fft, n)
    FFT.fft_forward(arena, g_fft, n)
    FFT.fft_forward(arena, F_fft, n)
    FFT.fft_forward(arena, G_fft, n)

    Note: 2x2 Gram of the row basis.  Per Pornin sign.c::expand_privkey,
    Note: gram_00 = |g|^2 + |f|^2 (row 0 norm squared), gram_11 = |G|^2 +
    Note: |F|^2 (row 1 norm squared), and gram_10 = G*conj(g) + F*conj(f)
    Note: (row 1 dot row 0 with the (-) signs cancelling).
    Let gram_00 be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bytes)
    Let gram_11 be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bytes)
    Let gram_10 be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bytes)
    If gram_10 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ldl_gram_diag with arena, g_fft, f_fft, n, gram_00
    proc ldl_gram_diag with arena, G_fft, F_fft, n, gram_11
    proc ldl_gram_off_diag with arena, G_fft, g_fft, F_fft, f_fft, n, gram_10

    Let node be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 64)
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ldl_tree_set_L01 with node, 0
    proc ldl_tree_set_D0 with node, 0
    proc ldl_tree_set_D1 with node, 0
    proc ldl_tree_set_left with node, 0
    proc ldl_tree_set_right with node, 0
    proc ldl_tree_set_n with node, n
    proc ldl_tree_set_is_leaf with node, 0

    Note: Top-level 2x2 LDL:
    Note:   L01_top[k] = gram_10[k] / gram_00[k]   (complex; g00 is real)
    Note:   D1_top[k]  = gram_11[k] - |gram_10[k]|^2 / gram_00[k]   (real)
    Let L01_top be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bytes)
    Let D1_top be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bytes)
    If D1_top is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kk be 0
    While kk is less than n:
        Let g00 be FFT.fft_get_real(gram_00, kk)
        Let g10r be FFT.fft_get_real(gram_10, kk)
        Let g10i be FFT.fft_get_imag(gram_10, kk)
        Let g11_v be FFT.fft_get_real(gram_11, kk)
        Let zero_v be FP.fp_zero()
        Let g00_is_zero be FP.fp_eq(g00, zero_v)
        Let l01r be zero_v
        Let l01i be zero_v
        Let new_d1 be g11_v
        If g00_is_zero is equal to 0:
            Set l01r to FP.fp_div(g10r, g00)
            Set l01i to FP.fp_div(g10i, g00)
            Let m_a be FP.fp_mul(g10r, g10r)
            Let m_b be FP.fp_mul(g10i, g10i)
            Let mag2 be FP.fp_add(m_a, m_b)
            Let drop be FP.fp_div(mag2, g00)
            Set new_d1 to FP.fp_sub(g11_v, drop)
        End If
        FFT.fft_set_real(L01_top, kk, l01r)
        FFT.fft_set_imag(L01_top, kk, l01i)
        FFT.fft_set_real(D1_top, kk, new_d1)
        FFT.fft_set_imag(D1_top, kk, zero_v)
        Set kk to kk plus 1
    End While

    proc ldl_tree_set_L01 with node, L01_top

    Note: Split d00 = gram_00 into (d00_e, d00_o) over K_{n/2}.
    Let d00_e be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, half_bytes)
    Let d00_o be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, half_bytes)
    If d00_o is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ldl_fft_split with arena, gram_00, n, d00_e, d00_o

    Note: Split d11 = D1_top into (d11_e, d11_o) over K_{n/2}.
    Let d11_e be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, half_bytes)
    Let d11_o be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, half_bytes)
    If d11_o is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ldl_fft_split with arena, D1_top, n, d11_e, d11_o

    Let left_child be proc ldl_internal with arena, d00_e, d00_o, half_n, n
    If left_child is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let right_child be proc ldl_internal with arena, d11_e, d11_o, half_n, n
    If right_child is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ldl_tree_set_left with node, left_child
    proc ldl_tree_set_right with node, right_child

    Return node
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
END falcon_ldl
==============================================================================
:End Note
